claim.claim-text:
2. A method for dealing with a request of an external device for obtaining image data sensed by an image sensing device via a network, comprising the steps of:
receiving, from an external device, a reservation command which designates image sensing time and requests the control apparatus to obtain image data at the image sensing time and to store the image data to be obtained in a memory;
notifying the external device of identification information identifying the image data to be obtained based on the reservation command, the reservation command of the external device being included in a URL indicating a location of the obtained image data;
determining whether or not a current time is the image sensing time designated by the reservation command received from the external apparatus;
controlling the image sensing device to sense an image in a case that it is determined that the current time is the image sensing time;
obtaining image data, at the image sensing time, sensed by the image sensing device, and storing the obtained image data in the memory; and
outputting the stored image data corresponding to identification information to the external device, in response to receiving the identification information from the external device.
